  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). Applicable requirement: the model shall predict relative hemolysis index (RH) within ±15% of experimental reference across all five flow-speed operating points (REQ-HEM-001). This requirement is documented inline within the package evidence but is not formally bound via bindsRequirement per the Minimal profile binding conventions.",
